# 📚 Document Butler – RAG API with FastAPI & React

A production‑ready **Retrieval‑Augmented Generation (RAG)** system that lets users upload documents (PDF, DOCX, MD, CSV, TXT), ask questions, and receive **streaming answers** with source citations. Built with FastAPI (backend), Qdrant (vector database), LangChain, and a modern dark‑theme React frontend.

![Demo](https://via.placeholder.com/800x400?text=Document+Butler+UI)

---

## ✨ Features

- **📄 Multi‑format upload** – PDF, DOCX, Markdown, CSV, TXT  
- **🔍 Semantic search** – Embeddings + Qdrant vector database  
- **💬 Streaming answers** – LLM responses token‑by‑token (SSE)  
- **📌 Source references** – Each answer includes the exact chunk, file name, page number, and relevance score  
- **🗂️ Document management** – List all uploaded documents, delete any document (removes all chunks)  
- **⚡ High performance** – Embedding model & LLM loaded once at startup (lifespan)  
- **🎨 Modern UI** – Dark theme, responsive, real‑time connection indicator  
- **🧪 Auto‑generated API docs** – Interactive Swagger UI at `/docs`

---

## 🏗️ Project Structure
fastapi_rag_project/
├── app/
│ ├── init.py
│ ├── config.py # Pydantic settings from .env
│ ├── file_loader.py # Multi‑format file loader
│ ├── rag_chain.py # Embeddings, Qdrant, indexing, query
│ ├── models.py # Pydantic request/response models
│ ├── api.py # Endpoint handlers
│ ├── routes.py # Route registration
│ └── state.py # Shared lifespan objects
├── uploads_tmp/ # Temporary storage (auto‑created)
├── uploads_original/ # Permanent original files
├── markdown_files/ # Generated markdown versions
├── .env # Environment variables (never commit)
├── main.py # FastAPI entry point
└── requirements.txt # Python dependencies

document-butler/ # React frontend
├── src/
│ ├── App.jsx
│ ├── DocumentButler.jsx # Main UI component
│ └── index.css
└── package.json

