## 🚀 Quick Start

### Prerequisites
- Python 3.10+
- Node.js 18+ & npm
- Qdrant Cloud account (free tier) – [https://cloud.qdrant.io](https://cloud.qdrant.io)
- OpenAI API key (if using OpenAI embeddings or LLM)

### 1. Clone & Backend Setup

```bash
git clone <your-repo-url>
cd fastapi_rag_project
python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate      # Windows: venv\Scripts\activate
pip install -r requirements.txt
2. Configure .env
Create a .env file in the backend root:

ini
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...
QDRANT_URL=https://your-cluster.cloud.qdrant.io:6333
QDRANT_API_KEY=your-api-key
QDRANT_COLLECTION=rag_docs

EMBEDDING_PROVIDER=huggingface   # or "openai"
LLM_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini

MAX_UPLOAD_SIZE_MB=50
UPLOAD_DIR=uploads_tmp
3. Run Backend
bash
python main.py
# Server runs at http://localhost:8000
# Swagger UI: http://localhost:8000/docs
4. Frontend Setup (separate terminal)
bash
cd ..
npm create vite@latest document-butler -- --template react
cd document-butler
npm install
Replace src/DocumentButler.jsx with the provided component (see below).
Update src/App.jsx:

jsx
import DocumentButler from './DocumentButler'
export default function App() { return <DocumentButler /> }
Set src/index.css to:

css
* { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }
body { overflow: hidden; }
5. Run Frontend
bash
npm run dev
# Open http://localhost:5173
